        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 12:42AM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 1242 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lone Hickory, or near Yadkinville, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Yadkinville...
East Bend...
Courtney...
Huntsville...
Shacktown...
Enon...
and Lone Hickory.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
